p.span: Sync implementation should record progress through different data syncing stages.

Upon recoverable errors or disconnects and reconnects, if syncing has not successfully completed all desired stages, sync implementation should resume to the syncing stage that was interrupted when device disconnected.
Order of syncing stages retrieving data depicted is not mandatory, applications are free to choose order that best fits their use case and usage pattern.
Retries and skipping rest of sync upon repeated timeouts for attempting to reconnect should be handled as well.

Some situations require user intervention. For example, pairing with user's phone needs to be performed in order to properly connect to device in some situations. In the context of background syncing, should the need to inform user about repeated failures to connect and appropriate recovery steps arises, a good strategy is e.g. inform user with platform specific notification.
